  "body": "### Description\n\nWhen you pass a null value as parameter to the SyntheticBeanBuildItem generation, you get a NullPointerException but you don't have any clue (at first) where the problem occured.\r\n\r\n```\r\nCaused by: java.lang.NullPointerException\r\n        at io.quarkus.gizmo.BytecodeCreatorImpl.allocateLocalVariables(BytecodeCreatorImpl.java:1195)\r\n        at io.quarkus.gizmo.MethodCreatorImpl.write(MethodCreatorImpl.java:122)\r\n        at io.quarkus.gizmo.ClassCreator.writeTo(ClassCreator.java:202)\r\n        at io.quarkus.gizmo.ClassCreator.close(ClassCreator.java:225)\r\n        at io.quarkus.arc.processor.BeanGenerator.generateSyntheticBean(BeanGenerator.java:222)\r\n\r\n```\r\nYou can trigger the above Exception by code like this\r\n\r\n```\r\n        return SyntheticBeanBuildItem.configure(Foo.class)\r\n                .scope(Singleton.class)\r\n                .creator(FooCreator.class)\r\n                .param(\"test\", (String)null)\r\n                .done();\r\n```\r\n\r\nOf course, in our extension the parameter test was based on some logic and it was not clear that the NPE was caused by passing `null` as value as it happens later and stacktrace is not related anymore to the problematic statement.\r\n\r\n\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\nAdd a proper check and exception to all `.param` overloaded methods to indicate null is not an allowed value.",
